Package: numVerDrvtn
Type: Package
Title: Numerically Verified Derivations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Mark", "Thallman", email = "mark.thallman@usda.gov",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides an S4 virtual class 'definedExpression' and supporting
    operators (':=', '.eq', '.eq.last') for conducting mathematical derivations
    in R with automatic numerical verification at each step. The ':=' operator
    assigns an expression and prints it, while the '. ==' construct compares a
    subsequent rearrangement against the previous result. Derivative
    verification infrastructure is provided via numerical Jacobians computed
    with the 'numDeriv' package. Any class (e.g., 'PartitionedMatrix', 'Matrix',
    numeric) can inherit from 'definedExpression' to gain these capabilities.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
